modules.description: Provides functions to create and configure fake functions that return specified values or raise exceptions, along with mechanisms to track and inspect their calls. Works with function types and references to capture argument patterns during execution. Useful for testing behavior of code that depends on external functions by simulating their responses.

Checks that a mock object's calls match an expected list or verify a single call with specific arguments, using custom comparison and printing functions. Operates on mock objects that track argument lists and return values. Used to validate interaction sequences in test cases involving mocked dependencies.
